<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Simple Selectors</title>
<style>
/*Element selector */
p {
   color: blue;
}
/*ID selector*/
#main {
      color: red;
}
/*Class selector*/
.note {
      color: green;
}
/*Group selector*/
h1, h2 {
        text-align: center;
}
/*Universal selector*/
* {
   font-family: Arial;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1 id="main">CSS Selectors</h1>
<h2>INTRODICTION</h2>

<p> SELECTOR FORMS.</p>
<p class="note">A CSS selector is used to select HTML elements so that we can apply styles(color, size, layout, etc.) to them.</p>

</body>
</html>
